{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:23:08.271075+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the README and `docs/sources.md`, here are all the external book sources the app reads from:\n\n| Source | Endpoint | Auth | Notes |\n|--------|----------|------|-------|\n| **Feedbooks (public)** | `https://catalog.feedbooks.com/catalog/public_domain.atom` | Anonymous (no key) | OPDS catalog |\n| **Project Gutenberg mirror** | `https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/...` | Anonymous (no key) | HTML scraping |\n| **Internet Archive Bookreader** | `https://archive.org/details/...` | Anonymous (no key) | OAuth **optional** for higher rate limits |\n| **Standard Ebooks** | `https://standardebooks.org/feeds/atom/all` | Anonymous (no key) | Atom feed |\n\n### Summary\n\n- **No source requires an API key or OAuth token for basic access** — all four sources are accessed anonymously by default.\n- The only optional auth is **Internet Archive**, which accepts OAuth to obtain higher rate limits, but it is not required.\n- The docs note that \"the only authentication some endpoints accept is a server-side rate-limit token shipped via CI secrets\" — meaning any rate-limit tokens are baked into CI, not user-provided credentials.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 495, "prompt_tokens": 8624, "total_tokens": 9119, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 235, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8064}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "9c2d7322fc7043efa3e17cce3c469b25", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead68-9943-79a2-909e-9e7823e923a9-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8624, "output_tokens": 495, "total_token